<title>Further changes of |xue</title>
<summary>|xue becomes a lizard, a <i>dui</i>, an Omuherero, a <i>shao</i> tree, a Makoba and <i>!naxane</i>, as the sun sets and rises. At one point |xue cries out and his wife takes hold of him. She gives her husband water and he dies, becoming a little bird. |xue&apos;s wife calls her mother and father to come and look at |xue, who becomes a little black ant. |xue&apos;s father-in-law seizes him and tries to burn him with fire. |xue leaps over the fire and his father-in-law chases him. |xue bites his father-in-law, who slaps him.</summary><comments>1) p.9380v: (27 March 1880); !nanni heard this story from his paternal grandfather (Karu), 2) p.9381v: the <i>shao</i> tree; a description of a man in a picture Lloyd showed to the boys; about <i>!naxane</i> trees, ground <i>!naxane</i>, and <i>!naxane</i> fruit, 3) p.9383v: other things that |xue becomes (a cat, a fly, great water and grass), 4) This story is found in Book XI &amp; XII-5</comments><date>27 March 1880 (started)</date><storypages>9380v, 9381-9384</storypages><category>Transformation</category><author>!nanni (XI)</author><keyword><kw>|xue</kw><subkw>his further changes</subkw></keyword>
